'''Taishi Nishiyama Kofun''' (太子西山古墳), also known as '''Okutsuki Kofun''' (奥城古墳), is a [[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]] located in [[:en:Taishi, Osaka|Taishi]], [[:en:Osaka Prefecture|Osaka Prefecture]], Japan. It is part of the {{ill|Isonokami Kofun Cluster|ja|磯長谷古墳群|1=Shinagadani Kofun Cluster|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isonokami Kofun Cluster|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinagadani Kofun Cluster|qq=}}.

While the actual occupants are unknown, the [[:en:Imperial Household Agency|Imperial Household Agency]] designates it as the joint burial tomb for [[Emperor Bidatsu]] and [[:en:Princess Ishi-hime|Princess Ishi-hime]] (Empress of [[:en:Emperor Kinmei|Emperor Kinmei]]).

== Overview ==
Taishi Nishiyama Kofun is a large [[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]] located on the foothills of [[:en:Mount Nijō|Mount Nijō]] in southeastern Osaka Prefecture. It was built at the saddle of a ridge extending north to south, west of the Hamuro settlement in Isonokami Valley, typeing part of the {{ill|Isonokami Kofun Cluster|ja|磯長谷古墳群|1=Shinagadani Kofun Cluster|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isonokami Kofun Cluster|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinagadani Kofun Cluster|qq=}}. It is the only [[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]] within this cluster<ref name="taishicho"/>. As it is Historic Site1 an imperial tomb, it is under the administration of the [[:en:Imperial Household Agency|Imperial Household Agency]], and no typeal excavation has been conducted to date.

The tumulus faces northwest, featuring a two-tiered mound construction<ref name="taishicho">{{Cite web|url=http://www.town.taishi.osaka.jp/kanko_info/rekishi_shiseki/bidatsutennoryo.html|title=Emperor Bidatsu's Tomb (Taishi Nishiyama Kofun)|publisher=Taishi Town Official Website}}</ref>. Haniwa fragments have been collected from the mound, and there is evidence of a surrounding moat<ref>{{Cite book|title=Isonokami Kofun Cluster - The Royal Tombs of Taishi Town|author=Taishi Town Board of Education|year=1994|pages=14–15}}</ref>. The burial facility is presumed to be a horizontal stone chamber<ref name="taishicho"/>.

Based on haniwa and other burial goods, the tumulus is estimated to have been constructed in the early part of the late [[Kofun period]]<ref name="taishicho"/>.

== area ==
The mound area are as follows<ref>{{Cite book|title=Japanese Historical Place names Encyclopedia, Osaka Prefecture|author=Heibonsha|year=1986|pages= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Isonokami Kofun Cluster - The Royal Tombs of Taishi Town|author=Taishi Town Board of Education|year=1994|pages=14–15}}</ref>:
* '''Mound length''': 113 m (or 93 m<ref name="taishicho"/>)
* '''Rear round section''': 
** Diameter: 58 m
* '''Front square section''': 
** Width: 67 m

== Occupants ==
The actual occupants of Taishi Nishiyama Kofun remain unknown. However, the [[:en:Imperial Household Agency|Imperial Household Agency]] designates it as the joint tomb of the 30th [[Emperor Bidatsu]] (崩御 in 585?) and his mother, [[:en:Princess Ishi-hime|Princess Ishi-hime]] (year of death unknown). The tomb is referred to as the {{ill|Taishi Nishiyama Kofun|lt=Taishi Nishiyama Kofun|lt=Kawachi Shinaga Naka no O Tomb|ja|河内磯長中尾陵|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawachi Shinaga Naka no O Tomb|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 太子西山古墳}} and {{ill|Shinaga Plain Tomb|ja|磯長原陵|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinaga Plain Tomb|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, respectively<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kunaicho.go.jp/ryobo/successive_list.html|title=List of Mausoleums|publisher=Imperial Household Agency}}</ref>.

If this tumulus is indeed Emperor Bidatsu's tomb, it would be the last [[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]] imperial tomb and the final [[kofun]] featuring [[:en:Haniwa|Haniwa]]<ref>{{Cite book|title=Isonokami Kofun Cluster - The Royal Tombs of Taishi Town|author=Taishi Town Board of Education|year=1994|pages=14–15}}</ref>. However, the presence of cylindrical haniwa casts doubt on its identification with Emperor Bidatsu's tomb<ref>{{Cite book|title=Japanese Historical Place names Encyclopedia, Osaka Prefecture|author=Heibonsha|year=1986}}</ref>. Some researchers suggest the actual tomb might be {{ill|Hamuro Kofun Group|lt=Hamuro Kofun Group|lt=Hamuro Kofun|ja|葉室塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamuro Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 葉室古墳群}}, also located in Taishi Town<ref>{{Cite book|title=Isonokami Kofun Cluster - The Royal Tombs of Taishi Town|author=Taishi Town Board of Education|year=1994|pages=38–41}}</ref>.

